    <p>Shaw The­atres is giv­ing away movie passes to Chi­nese movie The Eight Hun­dred, based on true events dur­ing the Sino-Ja­panese war in Shanghai, China, in 1937. Then, 400 sol­diers – called the Eight Hun­dred Heroes in his­tory – held the fort against nu­mer­ous waves of Ja­panese forces for four days and nights in a bid to pro­tect the Si­hang Ware­house. Par­tic­i­pants have to like, share and com­ment on the post on Shaw The­atres’ Face­book page and reg­is­ter their par­tic­u­lars at the link be­low. Five peo­ple will each win a pair of tick­ets.</p>
    <p>WHEN: To­day INFO: bit.ly/3lRkQ3U</p>


